LORE kowloon-warden
FLAGS KOWLOON GUARD
- Wardens of Iron: walls, gate discipline, armed response, militia training;
  officers rotate seasonally — no officer commands the same gate more than
  one season; prevents gate-specific loyalty cultivation
- Four gates: Jade (north, diplomatic). Iron (caravan frontier, heaviest
  traffic). Lantern (west, oil lamps left by returning travelers). Tide
  (harbor-facing, widest, cargo wagons and grain barges).
- Crimson flags from watchtowers = martial law zone; clear the street
- Execution Square: Executioner activated by tribunal seal only; for
  assassination in sanctuary, gate sabotage, theft from emergency reserves,
  or riot during flood alarm
- River Corsairs (Blacktide Shen) probe gate timings; movement reports worth
  coin; file at Iron Gate guardhouse
- After midnight: authorized personnel only; Courier Lantern runners carry
  brass lantern-badges granting passage; others face stop-and-identity
~
